                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1495-2">Assemani, ASMO, 54-59; BHO, 1149 ; Lagrange 61-64 ; Leclercq, III, 165-68.
AMS, II, 254-60.
Suhada ', I, 256-60.
Delehaye, Actes, 439- 44, 558- 59.
Wiessner, Miirtyrer, 144- 48.
Trad. anglaise dans Brock-Harvey, Holy Women, 73-76.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1495">After the execution of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/9">Simeon Bar Sabbaʿe</persName>, the wife of Shapur
          became sick. People accused the sister of Simeon, Tarbo, of witchcraft that caused the
          queen's sickness. Tarbo and her servant were arrested. They were tortured and cut into
          many pieces.</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">with Simeon Bar Sabbaʿe</note>
